    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-10T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-10T21:00:00-05:00" n="464"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/972: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-11T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 11, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 11—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. All foreign banks in Shanghai except Japanese have now made arrangements to
                    surrender silver to Central Bank either in accordance with the terms mentioned
                    in my 751, December 11, 5 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d464fn5">Not printed.</note>
                    or on basis of mutual deposits with Central Bank and foreign bank concerned in
                    place of deposit of securities equal to two-thirds of face value of silver
                    surrendered, the foreign bank’s deposit with the Central Bank to bear 6%
                    interest while the Central Bank’s deposit with foreign bank will draw 1%.
                    Understand slightly under 26,000,000 silver dollars surrendered while Japanese
                    banks still hold about 14,000,000.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping. Mail to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
